🤩 Must-try Thai food🔥 — I hit up @siamthai_nyc off a reco from my girl @ogmillie and had an amazing experience. Trendy ambiance, modern decor. You can book a private karaoke room, sing karaoke and eat! (Thai food in general is top three for me, fyi.) Pro tip: Family style + share for the best experience. 😋 — ps. RIP Charlie 🦀 😂

🇹🇭: @siamthai_nyc 
📍 Flushing, Queens

✨ HALAL SMOKEHOUSE ✨ — 📍Clifton, NJ — @kanoonsmokedmeat just opened up earlier this year. They mix Middle Eastern spices with smoky American BBQ — a diff type of smokehouse experience than I’m used to! — Def loved the short ribs. I heard the wings are bomb, but didn’t get a chance to order. Maybe next time! 🥹 Been seeing more and more diff type of halal restaurants open up in NJ! 🙌🏼 (ps. This audio was made for me. 😬) TY for the invite!

Birthdays go crazy. 🎈🥰

- Bday Eats: @overstory @crownshynyc (FiyahHhhh.)
- Turn Up Venue: @_titopapas 
- Photos: @imdesi.gner 
- Vibes: @uncrowndsounds 
- Bball: @swishhousefitnyc (Don’t judge, I’m out of shape. 😂) 
- Bagel: @peterpandonut 

Reels to come!

🏀 MSG Fave Eats 🤩 — Two yummy things that got me in a chokehold whenever I go to watch the Knicks play: 1.) Prime Rib Sandwich and 2.) Daily Burger — Food at MSG is unfortunately generally costly, but if you’re there to splurge you’ve gotta to try either one of these!!! — I dream about both of them often. 😂😍 Lmk if you have tried, or IF y’all try! — Ps. LFG Knicks!!! Nosebleed seats bc I had to ball out on this food. 😂😂😂

🔥 HALAL HOT CHICKEN 🔥 — Once upon a time I covered @eat.namkeen and their Pakistani x Nashville Hot Chicken Sandwich for NJ.com! — Food has always been fire, but have you ever tried their spicy maple wings??? Sheesh. 🤤 My new fave! Pretty dope to see local restaurants expand too (Chatham to Brooklyn and soon Metuchen). 😍

💕 DATE NIGHT SPOT 💕 — Marking some of my videos “date night” since y’all keep asking me for “impressive” or “bougie” date night spots. 😂🤣 — @overstory is easily one of my favorite bars… and also one of @theworlds50best favorite bars too. — Pretty dope to sip amazing cocktails on the 63rd floor of a FiDi skyscraper. It’s 1/3 of @chefjameskent ‘s trifecta — the other two being @crownshynyc + @saga_nyc ! Def. dope vibes for a date, from the music to ambiance and drink menu. They predominately play hip hop, including classic throwbacks. 😮‍💨😮‍💨— ps. Video coming soon on @crownshynyc ! 😍

🏀 BBALL + DONUTS 🍩 ‼️— 📍Brooklyn — @swishhousefitnyc is the only class that can get me up early enough to take a 7:30am workout class in Brooklyn coming from New Jersey. 😵‍💫 (Where my early birds at?? Lol.) — What makes the trip even more worth it is getting @peterpandonut after. This is literally my idea of a perfect Friday morning. 🥰 (Maybe add in a sunny afternoon at the beach afterwards to be even more perf. 😂) — I went to work after this though, lol. 😅 — Come take a class with me! #notSP #justfunAF
Like a moth to a flame, burned by the 🔥. — TY @janetjackson for sharing the stage with me last night. 😂#backupdancer  #quickphotodump

🧇 Catered Brunch 🔥 — Hosted a brunch at my crib for my loved ones, so had to make it special!! 🧡 Had an amazing experience with @constantinos.italian.market ! They can work with your budget for a delicious spread. Got a lot of compliments from my guests. 😍 Lmk if you have questions!

🤩 Directed my first celebrity shoot!! Can you guess who? 👀 — Can’t wait to show y’all the episode! Life’s dope. Sometimes I can’t distinguish fantasy from reality tbh. 😂 — TY @laurenxbrenner for the pics. 🔥 ps. Did you know oysters are an aphrodisiac?? 😂👀👅

💜 UBE HEAVEN 🙏🏻 — This NJ cafe has every ube treat imaginable. 😆 They also make their own ube halaya (purple yam jam lol) in house. — And sorry, there were too many desserts to label in this video. 😀 Iced ube float latte is a must, and I love their ube yam cookies. — Small world though: Found out I used to play bball with one of the owners, and work with the other owner’s mom. 😂🔥🤯 — 
Ps. Shirt is from @cambeezy_24 @misscierra10 !! Check out @bynumfaithfoundation, they’re doing amazing things for the Philippines. 🙏🏻🇵🇭💜😌

☕️ Pakistani cafe 🔥 — Chatham has some low key gems! From the crew behind @eat.namkeen, NJ now has @chashnichaico. (It’s actually next door.) Food was delish. 😋 That gulabi waffle tho! Such a perfect Sunday treat. 💜 ps. If you haven’t tried @eat.namkeen either, def go! (NJ and BK)

🇵🇭 Filipino food in NJ 🔥 — @qsina_8 is a new-ish local gem in Union, NJ! — Had a great time feastin’. I loved their desserts, sizzling Biko + ube flan turon. 🤤 Also some faves were Kare Kare (deconstructed), their noodle dishes are a must… and they also serve ube champorado on their breakfast menu. 👀 Enjoy!

Goodbye, Dream Job. 🥹 — Thank you @condenast x @bonappetitmag x @epicurious for trusting my creative vision as a Producer + Director. Met some of the dopest people, from coworkers to chefs to celebs. I never thought I’d part so soon — but sometimes bigger opportunities unexpectedly come your way. 🥹🙏🏻 Can’t wait to share the news. In the meantime, I’ll be unplugging and sipping cocktails on an island. 😂🍹

Horseshoe Bae 😂 — Bermuda reel coming soon! I only spent 1.5 days there. Attempted to visit the obligatory spots, but some things didn’t go according to plan. 🥹👀 — Gonna make sure y’all don’t make the same mistakes I made. 😭😬😅 #famtrip❤️ #JerseyShore 😂

👀 COMING SOON ‼️- Our @1950originals brick & mortar restaurant will be opening in Westwood, N.J. this FALL - the FIRST of its kind in the Northeast region! 🤯

Follow @1950originals for all updates, and sneak peeks!!! (We got A LOT of surprises in store for y’all.)

Message from our new President/CMO ➡️ I’m so excited to be joining @d_christopher_ and the talented 1950 Originals team. Can’t wait to help tell our story thru my foodie lens. 😌🎥 See ya soon, Westwood! - ❤️ @mel_vs_food

🤩 AYCE A5 Wagyu 👀 — @hyun_nyc is a wagyu lover’s dream come true. Option B included 15 different cuts plus marinated wagyu, 90 minutes to indulge AYCE for $165 pp. Definitely worth experiencing at least once. I was so full at the end!!! NGL, it’s a lot of heavy food!!! Enjoy. 😌

🥩 Hyun
📍10 E 33rd St, New York, NY 10016
💰$165 PP
🍽️ Option B Hyun-makase
💡Use Resy for a rezzy!

⭐️ Michelin Starred restaurant + hip hop vibes??? 😍 Sign me up!!! 🫶🏻 — Yes, it was worth it. Playlist was elite. Food was phenom. @crownshynyc is 1/3 of @chefjameskent ‘s 70 Pine trifecta in the financial district of NYC. It’s also worth checking out @saga_nyc and @overstory !!! 🔥 ps. I reco all three to people often! Have you been?? @tastemade 

👑 @crownshynyc 
📍70 Pine Street Ground Floor, New York, NY 10005
🍽️ Everything was good!
💡Saga + Overstory are on the 63rd floor! 🔥

🚀 SPACE THEMED HOT POT & BBQ 🤩 — @threehotpotbbq was worth the hype! $89.99 lunch special for four people, fun “out of this world” ambiance, and food was bomb. — Enjoy, eArrThLinggzzz! 👽🤣👽

🔥 @threehotpotbbq 
📍18 W. 38th St. New York, NY 10018
🍽️ $89.99 lunch special for 4 
💡It’s BYOB!!!

Pick your favorite Filipino Street Food 🔥🇵🇭 @dollarhits houses all your favorite Filipino street foods under one roof! You pick whatever you want and they grill them up for you fresh! 😋 

@mel_vs_food on the ground capturing footage at the New York location that opened after the success of the Los Angeles flagship!
“But this summer is different…” #thesummeriturnedhungry 🌭😂 #photodump

Trekked in this heat wave to the @bhphoto #bildexpo2023 to catch @omgadrian’s workshop! Def heard everything I needed to hear from a handful of amazing speakers. 🔥 Best of all, the event was Free 99! 😆 — Just a reminder: Never stop learning and trying to hone your craft! #reinspired ❤️
🎉 GRAND OPENING 🥳 — We’re excited to finally announce that we’ll be opening our doors on Sun. Oct. 15! 😉🌭 Who’s coming!?

🎃 SPOOKY SZN 🎃 — For those who are new here, please accept me for who I am. 🤣 — A look back at: 1.) Tina Belcher, 2.) Hip Hop Harry, 3.) Twerkin’ Inflatable Dancer, 4.) Ratchet Dora — What should I be this year? 👀😂

THIS SUNDAY!!! 🤩 — When you visit our @1950originals restaurant, just know: I drew all the cool shiiii. ✍️😂 I am so thankful for the support yall have shown!!! 🥺🤧 Not once have I told my friends to share a post, or plan to travel an hour away for our Grand Opening. So it hits even more. 😭🥺😭🙏🏻 (Brb crying.) — Our team has worked so hard on this. See yall Sunday! Take a pic with me pls. 🙏🏻 ps. To my friends who can’t make it out, no worries or pressure. I know you still support. ❤️ (Also, fyi, I plan on getting back to filming other food content real soon! TY for your patience! Lol.)

New milestones, who dis? 🔥 — A little photo dump of the past few weeks. 😵‍💫🌪️❤️ TY so much for those who have shown support for @1950originals in person or on IG! Means more than you’ll ever know. We’re officially open-open. 🔥

✈️ It’s time for that vacay to make it out the group chat. 😂 — This obviously depends on which holidays your job honors, but just giving you potential #options. — Thanks @tipsycritic for this! Real MVP. 💫
Celebrated our best gal’s bday with a charcuterie board (and onesie) party. 😍 Which board is your fave — is the the Pokéball one? Eh eh? 😂🤣 Happy bday, B! 😘

✨ NEW DATE NIGHT SPOT ✨ in New Jersey! @agavecantinamexicananj is the newer upscale spin off of @agavecocinamexicananj 🔥 Food was delish — Fave dish: Chamorro / Pork Shank 🤤 + Fave cocktail: Cielito Lindo (served in part of a Clase Azul bottle). Some nights there’s a DJ too! 🔥 Will def come back!

🇵🇭 Filipino Cafe Pop-Up 🇵🇭 — @ayalacoffee holds occasional pop ups at their shop! I caught two vendors there recently: @salvaje_htx + @vilma_nj. I haven’t had an OMG moment in a very long time, but I fell in LOVE with @salvaje_htx ube latte croissant (still dreaming of it) and @vilma_nj Filipino breakfast sandwich. That sandwich was so well balanced. A spam/longanisa patty with atchara (pickled papaya) that cut through the fat and provided a nice contrast. Then it came with this delicious garlic sauce, that definitely hit the Filipino breakfast feeling and taste. All sandwiched between flaky buttery croissant buns. And of course, I can’t leave Ayala without a Milo Banana Cold Brew.💡(Note: These treats aren’t always available! So you gotta follow them on IG to see who will pop up next!) Also worth mentioning: They’re expanding to a bigger location in Union — so exciting! 🤩
